VDH COVID Data by Age

Ryan Beck

Last updated: August 07, 2021

The plots below contain information about cumulative and weekly COVID cases, hospitalizations, and deaths by age group. The source data is from the Virginia Department of Health: https://data.virginia.gov/Government/VDH-COVID-19-PublicUseDataset-Cases_By-Age-Group/uktn-mwig.

Sometimes there is missing/choppy data. The reason for this is due to a quick attempt to clean up some clearly incorrect data that resulted in sudden spikes in the plots.

Click the code buttons to view the R code used.

library(RSocrata)
library(tidyverse)
library(zoo)
library(scales)
library(kableExtra)
library(reshape2)
library(latticeExtra)

df <- read.socrata("https://data.virginia.gov/resource/uktn-mwig.csv")

# this returns output that has for each date the number for each age group
df_grouped <- df %>% group_by(report_date,age_group_type,age_group) %>% summarise(across(c(number_of_cases, number_of_hospitalizations, number_of_deaths), sum))

# filters to get only regular age group type, not vaccine age group
df_filtered <- df_grouped %>% filter(age_group_type == "Case Age Group")

df_filtered <- df_filtered %>% mutate(report_date = as.Date(report_date,"%Y-%m-%d"))

cumulative_cases <- ggplot(df_filtered, aes(report_date, number_of_cases)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Cumulative Cases", title="Cumulative Virginia COVID Cases by Age Group") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(10000)) +
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))
  
cumulative_hospitalizations <- ggplot(df_filtered, aes(report_date, number_of_hospitalizations)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Cumulative Hospitalizations", title="Cumulative Virginia COVID Hospitalizations by Age Group") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(500)) +
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))

cumulative_deaths <- ggplot(df_filtered, aes(report_date, number_of_deaths)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Cumulative Deaths", title="Cumulative Virginia COVID Deaths by Age Group") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(500)) +
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))


#Find weekly values

#df_intermediate <- df_filtered %>% arrange(age_group, report_date)
#df_testing <- data.frame(df_intermediate[1:3],as.data.frame(lapply(df_intermediate[4:6], function(x) {
#  replace(x, x < lag(x,1), NA)
#})))
#df_testing <- df_testing %>% arrange(report_date)

final_table <- df_filtered %>% arrange(age_group, report_date)
final_table <- data.frame(final_table[1:3],as.data.frame(lapply(final_table[4:6], function(x) {
  replace(x, x < lag(x,1) | x > lag(x,1) + 2000, NA)
})))
final_table <- final_table %>% group_by(report_date, age_group) %>% transform(weekly_cases = number_of_cases - lag(number_of_cases,7), weekly_hospitalizations = number_of_hospitalizations - lag(number_of_hospitalizations,7),weekly_deaths = number_of_deaths - lag(number_of_deaths,7))
final_table <- final_table %>% arrange(report_date)
final_table <- select(final_table, -age_group_type)
final_table <- filter(final_table, age_group != "Missing")

weekly_cases <- ggplot(final_table, aes(report_date, weekly_cases,color=age_group)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Weekly Cases", title="Weekly Virginia COVID Cases by Age Group") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,NA)) + #breaks = breaks_width(10000),
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))

weekly_cases_zoom <- ggplot(final_table, aes(report_date, weekly_cases,color=age_group,shape=age_group)) +
  scale_shape_manual(values=1:10) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = age_group),size=3) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Weekly Cases", title="Weekly Virginia COVID Cases by Age Group - Since July 2021") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,2500)) + #breaks = breaks_width(10000),
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y"),limits = c(as.Date("2021-07-01"),NA)) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))

weekly_hospitalizations <- ggplot(final_table, aes(report_date, weekly_hospitalizations,color=age_group)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Weekly Hospitalizations", title="Weekly Virginia COVID Hospitalizations by Age Group") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,NA)) + #breaks = breaks_width(10000),
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))

weekly_hospitalizations_zoom <- ggplot(final_table, aes(report_date, weekly_hospitalizations,color=age_group,shape=age_group)) +
  scale_shape_manual(values=1:10) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = age_group),size=3) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Weekly Hospitalizations", title="Weekly Virginia COVID Hospitalizations by Age Group - Since July 2021") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,100)) + #breaks = breaks_width(10000),
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y"),limits = c(as.Date("2021-07-01"),NA)) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))

weekly_deaths <- ggplot(final_table, aes(report_date, weekly_deaths,color=age_group)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Weekly Deaths", title="Weekly Virginia COVID Deaths by Age Group") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,NA)) + #breaks = breaks_width(10000),
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey"))

weekly_deaths_zoom <- ggplot(final_table, aes(report_date, weekly_deaths,color=age_group,shape=age_group)) +
  scale_shape_manual(values=1:10) +
  geom_line(aes(color = age_group), size=1.2) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = age_group),size=3) +
  labs(x="Date", y="Weekly Deaths", title="Weekly Virginia COVID Deaths by Age Group - Since July 2021") +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,25)) + #breaks = breaks_width(10000),
  scale_x_date(breaks="1 month",labels = date_format("%b/%y"),limits = c(as.Date("2021-07-01"),NA)) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
